msgid "If you'd like to use this along with other tools for hardening, refer back to the [Apache Hardened Web Server guide](index.md). This document also uses all of the assumptions and conventions outlined in that original document, so it is a good idea to review it before continuing.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "One thing that is missing with _mod\\_security_ when installed from the generic Rocky Linux repositories, is that the rules installed are minimal at best. To get a more extensive package of free mod_security rules, we are using [Comodo's](https://www.comodo.com/) WAF installation procedure after installing the base package.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "Note that Comodo is a business that sells lots of tools to help secure networks. The free _mod\\_security_ tools may not be free forever and they do require that you setup a login with Comodo in order to gain access to the rules.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing mod_security"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "To install the base package, use this command which will install any missing dependencies. We also need _wget_ so if you haven't installed it, do that as well:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:38
#, no-wrap
msgid "dnf install mod_security wget\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting Up Your Comodo account"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "To setup your free account, go to [Comodo's WAF site](https://waf.comodo.com/), and click the \"Signup\" link at the top of the page. You will be required to setup username and password information, but no credit-card or other billing will be done.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "The credentials that you use for signing on to the web site will be used in your setup of Comodo's software and also to obtain the rules, so you will need to keep these safe in a password manager somewhere.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please note that the \"Terms and Conditions\" section of the form that you need to fill out to use Comodo Web Application Firewall (CWAF) is written to cover all of their products and services. That said, you should read this carefully before agreeing to the terms!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing CWAF"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "Before you start, in order for the script to actually run after we download it, you are going to need some development tools. Install the package with:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "dnf group install 'Development Tools'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:59
#, no-wrap
msgid "In addition, you will need to have your web server running for Comodo to see _mod\\_security_ correctly. So, start it if it is not already running:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "After signing up with Comodo, you will get an email with instructions on what to do next. Essentially, what you need to do is to login to the web site with your new credentials and then download the client install script.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "From the root directory of your server, use the wget command to download the installer:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "wget https://waf.comodo.com/cpanel/cwaf_client_install.sh\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "Run the installer by typing:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "bash cwaf_client_install.sh\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "This will extract the installer and start the process, echoing to the screen. You'll get a message part way down:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "No web host management panel found, continue in 'standalone' mode? [y/n]:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:85
#, no-wrap
msgid "Type \"y\" and let the script continue.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:87
#, no-wrap
msgid "You may also get this notice:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:88
#, no-wrap
msgid "Some required perl modules are missed. Install them? This can take a while. [y/n]:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:93
#, no-wrap
msgid "If so type \"y\" and allow those missing modules to install.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:94
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enter CWAF login: username@domain.com\n"
"Enter password for 'username@domain.com' (will not be shown): *************************\n"
"Confirm password for 'username@domain.com' (will not be shown): ************************\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:101
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please note here that you will probably have to download the rules and install them in the correct location, as the password field requires a punctuation or special character, but the configuration file apparently has issues with this when sending it to Comodo's site from the installer or update script.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:103
#, no-wrap
msgid "These scripts will always fail with a credentials error. This probably doesn't affect administrators who have web servers running with a GUI front end (Cpanel / Plesk) but if you are running the program standalone as we are in our example, it does. [You can find the workaround below](#cwaf_fix).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:104
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enter absolute CWAF installation path prefix (/cwaf will be appended): /usr/local\n"
"Install into '/usr/local/cwaf' ? [y/n]:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:110
#, no-wrap
msgid "Just accept the path as given and then type \"y\" in the next field for the install path.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:112
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you have a non-standard path to the configuration file for Apache/nginx, you would enter it here, otherwise just hit 'Enter' for no changes:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:113
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you have non-standard Apache/nginx config path enter it here:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "Here is where the failure comes in, and the only workaround is to manually download and install the rules. Answer the prompts as shown below:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "Do you want to use HTTP GUI to manage CWAF rules? [y/n]: n\n"
"Do you want to protect your server with default rule set? [y/n]: y\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "But expect to get the next message as well:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:126
#, no-wrap
msgid " Warning! Rules have not been updated. Check your credentials and try again later manually\n"
"+------------------------------------------------------\n"
"| LOG : Warning! Rules have not been updated. Check your credentials and try again later manually\n"
"+------------------------------------------------------\n"
"| Installation complete!\n"
"| Please add the line:\n"
"|   Include \"/usr/local/cwaf/etc/modsec2_standalone.conf\"\n"
"| to Apache config file.\n"
"| To update ModSecurity ruleset run\n"
"|   /usr/local/cwaf/scripts/updater.pl\n"
"| Restart Apache after that.\n"
"| You may find useful utility /usr/local/cwaf/scripts/cwaf-cli.pl\n"
"| Also you may examine file\n"
"|   /usr/local/cwaf/INFO.TXT\n"
"| for some useful software information.\n"
"+------------------------------------------------------\n"
"| LOG : All Done!\n"
"| LOG : Exiting\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:148
#, no-wrap
msgid "That's a little frustrating. You can go to your account on the Comodo web site and change your password and re-run the install script, BUT it won't change anything. The credentials will still fail.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:149
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"cwaf_fix\"></a> CWAF Rules File Workaround"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:152
#, no-wrap
msgid "To fix this, we need to manually install the rules from the web site. This is done by logging into your account on https://waf.comodo.com and clicking on the the \"Download Full Rule Set\" link. You'll then need to copy the rules to your web server using scp'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:155
#, no-wrap
msgid "scp cwaf_rules-1.233.tgz root@mywebserversdomainname.com:/root/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:160
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once the tar gzip file has been copied over, move the file to the rules directory:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:161
#, no-wrap
msgid "mv /root/cwaf_rules-1.233.tgz /usr/local/cwaf/rules/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "Then navigate to the rules directory:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:167
#, no-wrap
msgid "cd /usr/local/cwaf/rules/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:172
#, no-wrap
msgid "And uncompress the rules:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:173
#, no-wrap
msgid "tar xzvf cwaf_rules-1.233.tgz\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:178
#, no-wrap
msgid "Any partial updates to the rules will have to be handled in the same way.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:180
#, no-wrap
msgid "This is where paying for rules and support can come in handy. It all depends on your budget.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:181
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring CWAF"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:184
#, no-wrap
msgid "When we installed _mod\\_security_, the default configuration file was installed in `/etc/httpd/conf.d/mod_security.conf`. The next thing we need to do is to modify this in two places. Start by editing the file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "vi /etc/httpd/conf.d/mod_security.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:190
#, no-wrap
msgid "At the very top of the file, you will see:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:191
#, no-wrap
msgid "<IfModule mod_security2.c>\n"
"    # Default recommended configuration\n"
"    SecRuleEngine On\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:198
#, no-wrap
msgid "Beneath the `SecRuleEngine On` line add `SecStatusEngine On` so that the top of the file will now look like this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:199
#, no-wrap
msgid "<IfModule mod_security2.c>\n"
"    # Default recommended configuration\n"
"    SecRuleEngine On\n"
"    SecStatusEngine On\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:207
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next go to the bottom of this configuration file. We need to tell _mod\\_security_ where to load the rules. You should see this at the bottom of the file before you make changes:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:208
#, no-wrap
msgid "    # ModSecurity Core Rules Set and Local configuration\n"
"\tIncludeOptional modsecurity.d/*.conf\n"
"\tIncludeOptional modsecurity.d/activated_rules/*.conf\n"
"\tIncludeOptional modsecurity.d/local_rules/*.conf\n"
"</IfModule>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:217
#, no-wrap
msgid "We need to add in one line at the bottom to add the CWAF configuration, which in turn loads the CWAF rules. That line is `Include \"/usr/local/cwaf/etc/cwaf.conf\"`. The bottom of this file should look like this when you are done:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:218
#, no-wrap
msgid "    # ModSecurity Core Rules Set and Local configuration\n"
"\tIncludeOptional modsecurity.d/*.conf\n"
"\tIncludeOptional modsecurity.d/activated_rules/*.conf\n"
"\tIncludeOptional modsecurity.d/local_rules/*.conf\n"
"   \tInclude \"/usr/local/cwaf/etc/cwaf.conf\"\n"
"</IfModule>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:228
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now save your changes (with vi it's `SHIFT+:+wq!`) and restart httpd:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:234
#, no-wrap
msgid "If httpd starts OK, then you are ready to start using _mod\\_security_ with the CWAF.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:238
#, no-wrap
msgid "_mod\\_security_ with CWAF is another tool that can be used to help harden an Apache web server. Because CWAF's passwords require punctuation and because the standalone installation does not send that punctuation correctly, managing CWAF rules requires logging into the CWAF site and downloading rules and changes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:240
#, no-wrap
msgid "_mod\\_security_, like other hardening tools, has the potential of false-positive responses, so you must be prepared to tune this tool to your installation.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache_hardened_webserver/modsecurity.md:241
#, no-wrap
msgid "Like other solutions mentioned in the [Apache Hardened Web Server guide](index.md), there are other free and fee-based solutions for _mod\\_security_ rules, and for that matter, other WAF applications available. You can take a look at one of these at [Atomicorp's _mod\\_security_ site](https://atomicorp.com/atomic-modsecurity-rules/).\n"
msgstr ""

